The evidence with the title 'Dollar devaluation since 1913 - compare gold and silver prices ' says Jan 23, 2012  ... Since the Federal Reserve took over the US banking system in 1913 , the dollar has lost over 96 % of its value.  ... The value of a currency is also referred to as purchasing power .  ... Dollars in circulation , but just because there is more paper money floating around , that doesn't mean value has been created. 
